window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>All Michael Hollister wanted was death. What he got was time travel.</p> <p>Convicted of murder, and with nothing left to live for, Michael commits suicide in his jail cell in 1977, then opens his eyes in 1966, in his eight-year-old body, with all memories of his previous life intact.</p> <p>His first thoughts are of the dark intentions of his father. When the man who raised him once again tries to do the unthinkable, Michael has a chance to right his childhood's greatest wrong. But, can he do that without becoming a killer all over again?</p> <p>Includes a special bonus note read by the author.</p>"; 
